## Variable Descriptions

### Facebook Configuration
# FACEBOOK_PAGE_ACCESS_TOKEN: Long-lived page access token for your Facebook Page.
#   Generate this in Facebook App Settings → Messenger → Access Tokens.
# FACEBOOK_VERIFY_TOKEN: Custom token you create for webhook verification.
#   Must match the token you set in Facebook App webhook settings.
# FACEBOOK_APP_SECRET: Optional. Used for signature verification of incoming webhook requests.

### Supabase Configuration
# SUPABASE_URL: Your Supabase project URL. Found in Project Settings → API.
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY: Service role key (has admin privileges).
#   Found in Project Settings → API. **Keep this secret!**

### PydanticAI Gateway Configuration
# PYDANTIC_AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY: API key for PydanticAI Gateway (starts with paig_).
#   Get from your PydanticAI Gateway account.
# DEFAULT_MODEL: Default LLM model to use via PAIG.
#   Format: gateway/provider:model-name (e.g., gateway/openai:gpt-4o)
# FALLBACK_MODEL: Fallback model if primary model fails.
#   Format: gateway/provider:model-name (e.g., gateway/anthropic:claude-3-5-sonnet-latest)

### OpenAI Configuration
# OPENAI_API_KEY: API key for OpenAI (used as fallback when Copilot is unavailable).
#   Get from https://platform.openai.com/api-keys

### Environment
# ENV: Current environment. Options: local, railway, prod.
#   Used for environment-specific behavior.

### Sentry Configuration
# SENTRY_DSN: Sentry Data Source Name for error tracking and monitoring.
#   Get from https://sentry.io/settings/[org]/projects/[project]/keys/
#   Optional - if not provided, Sentry will not be initialized.
# SENTRY_TRACES_SAMPLE_RATE: Sample rate for performance monitoring traces.
#   Range: 0.0 (no traces) to 1.0 (all traces). Default: 1.0.

### Logfire Configuration
# LOGFIRE_TOKEN: Authentication token for Pydantic Logfire cloud logging.
#   Get from https://logfire.pydantic.dev/
#   Optional - if not provided, Logfire uses local console logging.
#   Pairs with PydanticAI Gateway for AI observability.

## Security Notes
# - Never commit .env file to version control
# - Use .env.example as a template only
# - Rotate secrets regularly
# - Use different tokens/keys for different environments
